<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="74" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="74">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="74">
Sexual morph not observed. Asexual morph: Conidiomata pycnidial, pulvinate, occurring separately, bright yellow to orange, immersed in bark, 400-600 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
high, 900-2200 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
diam.; wall of several layers of brown textura angularis; central column beneath the disc irregular, pale yellow. Conidiophores reduced to conidiogenous cells. Conidiogenous cells lining the inner walls of the cavity, hyaline, smooth, subcylindrical to ampulliform, 3-10 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-3.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
. Conidia hyaline, aseptate, smooth, multiguttulate, thin-walled, ellipsoid, straight to curved, (9.3
<normalizedToken originalValue="–)10.4–12.3(–">-)10.4-12.3(-</normalizedToken>
13.3) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(2.1
<normalizedToken originalValue="–)2.2–2.7(–">-)2.2-2.7(-</normalizedToken>
2.9) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, l/w = (3.4
<normalizedToken originalValue="–)4.2–5.2(–">-)4.2-5.2(-</normalizedToken>
5.9) (n = 50).
</paragraph>
